etymologies: Middle English: from Old French rondel, from ro(u)nd- (see round)

definitions: a small disk, especially a decorative medallion.
a picture or pattern contained in a circle.
shortDefinitions: picture or pattern contained in circle

definitions: a plain filled circle as a charge (often with a special name according to color).
a circular identifying mark painted on military aircraft, as, for example, the red, white, and blue of the RAF.
shortDefinitions: circular identifying mark painted on military aircraft

definitions: a short poem consisting of three stanzas of three lines each, rhyming alternately, with the opening words repeated as a refrain after the first and third stanzas. The form, a variant of the rondeau, was developed by Swinburne.
shortDefinitions: short poem consisting of three stanzas of three lines each, rhyming alternately, with opening words repeated as refrain
